When building with system abseil (GRPC_PYTHON_BUILD_SYSTEM_ABSL=True),
do not compile the vendored third_party/abseil-cpp/absl/log/initialize.cc.
The system abseil-cpp already provides this symbol, and the vendored file
does not exist when git submodules are not initialized.

Introduced by grpc/grpc#41639 in v1.78.1, which added a hardcoded
dependency on the vendored abseil initialize.cc outside the existing
BUILD_WITH_SYSTEM_ABSL filter that already handles CORE_C_FILES.

Upstream issue: https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/41696

--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -515,7 +515,7 @@
                 + list(CYTHON_HELPER_C_FILES)
                 + core_c_files
                 + asm_files
-                + ["third_party/abseil-cpp/absl/log/initialize.cc"]
+                + ([] if BUILD_WITH_SYSTEM_ABSL else ["third_party/abseil-cpp/absl/log/initialize.cc"])
             ),
             include_dirs=list(EXTENSION_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES),
             libraries=list(EXTENSION_LIBRARIES),
